cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new deep learning architecture for semantic segmentation of retinal layers and fluid masses in eye OCT scans. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning also suggests the possibility of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) being a relevant sub-category. The paper deals with medical imaging, which could be classified under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of a joint loss function and optimization suggests the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE).
